'''贾格纳寺'''（Shree Jagannath Temple）是一座重要的[[印度教|印度教]]寺庙，供奉[[毗湿奴|毗湿奴]]的一个化身贾格纳，位于印度东海岸[[奥里萨邦|奥里萨邦]]的[[普里|普里]]。目前的寺庙从10世纪开始，由[[东恒伽王朝|东恒伽王朝]]的建立者阿南泰伐摩·朱达恒伽提婆创建<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.asianart.com/articles/patachitra/index.html#4 |title=Bernard Cesarone: Pata-chitras of Odisha |first=Bernard |last=Cesarone |work=asianart.com |year=2012 |quote=This temple was built in approximately 1135-1150 by Codaganga, a king of the Eastern Ganga dynasty |accessdate=2 July 2012 |archive-date=2012-09-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120923063936/http://www.asianart.com/articles/patachitra/index.html#4 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

贾格纳寺以其每年一度的[[乘車節|乘車節]]而著名。<ref name="Nugteren 2010 159–172">{{cite journal |last=Nugteren |first=Albertina |title=Weaving Nature into Myth: Continuing Narratives Of Wood, Trees, And Forests In The Ritual Fabric Around The God Jagannath In Puri |journal=Journal for the Study of Religion, Nature and Culture |year=2010 |volume=4 |issue=2 |pages=159–172 |doi=10.1558/jsrnc.v4i2.159}}</ref>。

